# ============================================================
# PRO TIPS
# ============================================================

✔ Always check **Entropy** first.

✔ A **high entropy (>7)** often indicates packing or encryption.

✔ If a file is packed (e.g., UPX), unpack it before deeper analysis.

✔ Use **DIE + strings + file + sha256sum** together for a quick first look.

✔ Export JSON (`diec -j`) if you want structured output for reports or automation.
